name: jumping_jacks.gif
info: Jumping jack is a cardiovascular, full body warm up exercise as it helps loosening of the muscles.
howTo:
Stand upright. Your feet should be together and your hands by your sides. Begin exercise by raising both your hands simultaneously, up and above your head. While raising your hands jump off the floor and move your feet apart to a distance around twice that of shoulder width.
With your hands at the top and feet spread apart, immediately reverse your movement back to the starting position. Do this exercise in a fluid motion.
correctForm:
Try to synchronize the movement of your hands with your feet
Do not pause during this exercise

tts.text: Jumping Jacks is a very good full body warm up exercise

name: raised_arm_circles1.gif
info: Raised arm circle is a warm up exercise that targets your shoulders, back, biceps & triceps.
howTo: Stand straight and extend arms to the side without bending elbows. Start rotating arms in circle, complete set in one direction and then rotate them backwards.
correctForm:
Keep your arms & back straight
Keep your body in T formation during exercise

name: triceps_dips1.gif
howTo: Position your hands shoulder-width apart on a secured bench or stable chair.Slide your butt off the front of the bench with your legs extended out in front of you.Straighten your arms, keeping a little bend in your elbows to keep tension on your triceps and off your elbow joints.Slowly bend your elbows to lower your body toward the floor until your elbows are at about a 90-degree angle. Be sure to keep your back close to the bench.Once you reach the bottom of the movement, press down into the bench to straighten your elbows, returning to the starting position. This completes one rep.

name: wall_push_ups1.gif
howTo: Stand in front of a wall one big step away from it. Then put your hands out straight towards the wall and lean against it. Slowly bend your elbows and press your upper body towards the wall. Push back and repeat the exercise. Remember to keep your body straight.

name: push_up_knee1.gif
howTo: Start at the top of the push up position with your hands on the floor, arms straight and underneath your shoulders. Step your knees back behind you so that there is a straight line through your body from your knees up to your head. Engage your glutes, tense your legs and brace your core to keep your body rigid.

name: tricep_stretch1.gif
info: Tricep stretch is a great way to improve your upper body’s flexibility and strengthen shoulders.
howTo: Stand straight with your feet shoulder width apart, raise and bend one arm so your hand is in the middle of upper back. Grasp your elbow with the other hand and pull gently to feel stretch in tricep. Hold the stretch then repeat on the other side.
correctForm:
Keep your neck & shoulders relaxed
Exhale as you stretch, inhale as you release the stretch

name: push_up1.gif
info: Pushup is an effective exercise that primarily strengthens your chest, abs and core body muscles.
howTo: Position your hands and arms right below your shoulders while holding your body in a plank position. Lower your body until your chest is two inches above the floor. Then push your torso away from the ground until your arms lock, then repeat.
correctForm:
Keep your body in a straight position, don’t arch your back
Keep your core engaged throughout the entire movement

tts.text: Push Up is very effective exercise for upper body conditioning and core abs muscles

name: plank1.gif
info: Elbow plank is a calisthenics exercise that primarily targets the core abs muscles. It also targets the lower back and shoulders.
howTo: Go down to the floor like assuming a push up position. Instead of putting your hands on the floor, rest your body weight on elbow and forearms and keep them flat on the floor. Raise your hips off the floor in such a way that your entire body from head to heals form a straight line. You should feel tension in your core, hamstring and glutes.
correctForm:
Keep your hips in a flat position not too high not to low. Do not arch your back
Neck and head position should lie on a straight line

tts.text: Plank targets the core and upper abs muscles

name: plank_jump_ins1.gif
info: Plank jump ins is an advanced exercise like burpees that works on your abs and create core stability.
howTo: Get settled in a pushup position and wide your feets parallel to your shoulder width. Then jump your feets towards hands so your legs can unfurl and back again. This completes on repetition.
correctForm:
Keep your hips at the same height as your shoulders
Don’t arch your back

tts.text: Plank Jump Ins targets the core and lower abs muscles in addition to lower back and glutes

name: raised_leg_circles1.gif
info: Raised legs circle exercise in an easy way to harden your lower abs and strengthen front hip flexors.
howTo: Lying your back with both legs straight, put your hands underneath your lower back core for support. Use your feet to draw a larger circle as you can control from above your hips to close the ground as you can. Continue the motion with set of repetitions.
correctForm:
Do not let lower back peel up off the mat as you lower your legs
Breathe deeply into your back and sides

tts.text: Raised Leg Circles targets all abs muscle groups

name: mountain_climbers1.gif
info: Mountain climber is a very effective full body cardiovascular exercise. It is a compound exercise that targets the abs, lower back, hamstring,quads and triceps muscles.
howTo: Start in a plank position and keep your body straight. Begin pulling your right knee towards your chest. Maintain plank position. Keep the tension in your abs by pulling them in. Try to bring your knee in as close to the chest as you comfortably can. Once right knee has been pulled in repeat this movement with the other leg. Pull the left knee in and push the right leg out. Alternate these movement by switching between knees in a continuous motion.
correctForm:
Your hips should not drop nor your back should arch
Prevent your head from dropping

tts.text: Mountain Climbers is a full body exercise which targets shoulder chest and lower ab muscles

name: march_jacks1.gif
info: March jacks is a warm up exercise that primarily targets your abs, shoulders and thigh muscles.
howTo: Stand straight and raise arms upwards parallel to your body with one thigh lift with knee bend that nearly touches your torso. Then bring your arms and leg back together to starting position and repeat the motion with other leg.
correctForm:
Keep your body in straight position, don’t arch your back
Keep your head and neck straight

name: torso_rotation1.gif
info: Torso rotation engages your core body muscles that primarily includes your abs and back.
howTo: Stand upright with holding both hands together. Rotate your torso out at one side while placing your hands on top of each other. Then rotate back to opposite direction. This completes one repetition.
correctForm:
Keep lower body static
Keep feets at shoulder width part

name: cobra_stretch.gif
info: Cobra stretch helps strengthening muscles of arms, shoulders, chest and abdominals.
howTo: Lie face down on the floor with parallel thigh placement and place your hands underneath your shoulders. Start straightening your arms with chest lift and maintain a comfortable height of torso. Relax and hold the stretch upwards.
correctForm:
Tit head back and look upkeep
Keep your abs and back relaxed

name: donkey_kick_left.gif
howTo: Start on all fours with your knees under your butt and your hands under your shoulders. Then lift your left leg and squeeze your butt as much as you can. Go back to the start position and repeat the exercise.

name: donkey_kick_right.gif
howTo: Start on all fours with your knees under your butt and your hands under your shoulders. Then lift your right leg and squeeze your butt as much as you can. Go back to the start position and repeat the exercise.
